title: Print, "Title Page, Vasses de la Maison Royalle de L'oo Nouvellement (Vessels of the Royal House of L'oo)", ca. 1700
medium: Etching and engraving on white laid paper
inscribed: Inscribed in plate, in cartouche, lower center: Vasses / de la Maison Royalle / de L'oo / Nouvelle.mt inventé et Gravée / par Marot arch.te de sa / Majesté Britanique.; lower left: avec Previllege des Etats Generaux de Province Unie.
creditline: Museum purchase from General Acquisitions Endowment Fund
description: A monument decorated with garlands, foliage, and masks is mounted on a platform and topped with a bust of a man. Over the monument hangs drapery; two figures can be seen next to it, behind which is a rounded colonnade.

tombstone.epitaph:
Print, "Title Page, Vasses de la Maison Royalle de L'oo Nouvellement (Vessels of the Royal House of L'oo)", ca. 1700.
ca. 1700. Etching and engraving on white laid paper. Museum purchase from General Acquisitions Endowment Fund. 1988-4-32.
